caption: Last weekend we drove to BK lobster in Williamsburg, unfortunately after driving around for more than an hour unable to find parking we had to leave without satisfying our hunger with the lobster roll our stomachs were waiting for. This weekend we decided to try another location closer to home and we were successful finally. My daughter had the classic lobster roll and I had the salmon roll and they were both disappointing. Both were very bland except for the excessive salt, on the rolls as well as the fries. We are really trying to support black owned businesses, but the quality of the food has to be comparable or better than fast food chains. I could have gotten better food for less else where. I took two bites of my roll and threw the rest out. My daughter was so hungry she forced herself to eat half of hers but she said it was nasty. I would not recommend this to anyone.
I actually liked their food and service, awesome location very close to my house. The cashiers are always friendly. Will visit here again.

Super excited to try for the first time, highly disappointed. I visited the Myrtle Avenue location and purchased the Bed-stuy Biggie and the Classic BK Lobster Roll which cost me 50.00 dollars. While I did not expect to have a pound of lobster on the rolls but I surely expected more than a tablespoon full for that amount of money. In addition, both sandwiches were extremely salty and just poorly prepared. I Love supporting our local shops but I don’t think I will be returning
Love the food! Very courteous place.
I can’t even taste the seafood due to the amount of sodium.  The takeouts was way too salty and the package tartar sauce is insulting for the money spent.

This was my first time eating from here. The food was delicious. The only down side is no over the phone ordering, which would have saved the wait time.They use doordash, uber eats, etc but when I tried to order , they said I live too far. I only live 3.5 miles away. Overall,  I was very satisfied.
The food was excellent. Just the atmosphere was off. Because of covid. I traveled from NJ to Bk to enjoy good food.  Big Shout out to the owner. Rodney B.
garbage save your money, skinny girl up front was very rude, was bothered because I interpreted her phone call , didn't feel welcomed, plus my lobster roll had hardly any lobster. 2/23/21

This was my first time eating at BK Lobster. The food looked amazing in pictures so I couldn’t wait to indulge. Unfortunately the food did not live up to the pics. The food was flavorless and misleading. I ordered the lobster bisque with lump crab. Their “lump crab” looked like tiny pieces of tuna fish and the soup tasted like canned soup. The lobster in the Connecticut roll was over cooked, it was tough and rubbery. My friend ordered the lobster Mac and cheese and there was barely any lobster in it and the zesty corn was trash as well. The place looks nice, but the food was subpar unfortunately.
I had a large lobster roll and french fries.  It was worth every penny.  I thoroughly enjoyed it.
I like the BLT lobster sandwich
Yassss

The food was totally edible, definitely get the lobster cheddar biscuits. The lobster mac and cheese serving size is quite small so be warned.  No one in the establishment was wearing masks and I don't know why, so be warned if you wanted to walk in.

First off the lobster roll was good I had the classic but they definitely played themselves with that lobster Mac & cheese. Barely had any lobster in it I could count about 4 pieces of lobster that were definitely scraps even the portion of Mac & cheese wasn’t worth the money. Smh pride yourself on being a black own business but giving out scraps!!

Got the Crown Heights Fried Lobster, Lobster loaded fries and Grande Lobster Cheddar biscuit. Only problem was with delivery. The food wasn’t labeled so we had to figure out which box belonged to who.

You pay over $20 for literally 1 bite of meat. This is atrocious. Its literally like lobster salad. Its not even chunky meat from a lobster. DO NOT GO HERE. I PROMISE IF YOU ENJOY LOBSTER YOU WILL BE DISAPPOINTED. I honestly hope they shut down because of Covid because this is so wrong.
Staff & Service was Great! Had the Biggie (Big Poppa) it was very tasty.
Loved BKLobster they ladies treated us very good, food was amazing

What a let down... I ordered a Biggie lobster roll which was supposed to be a 1 1/2 lobster on a roll instead I received  a skimpy portion of lobster that was overcooked as well as over priced at $28 dollars. (Won't catch me twice)

Not sure why there’s a vegan bacon option online but I was curious to see how’d that’d go with a salmon roll. I put  lobster allergy which simply means try not to get any lobster into my food. Simple. Change gloves move to another table. They refunded my order and delivered my boyfriends food then “closed” Learn how to service your allergy costumers By simply following doh guidelines learn how to maintain your online menu!! This way you won’t have to turn down a loyal costumer.  you saw vegan and allergy on one order and got intimidated. Possibly Due to lack of knowledge. Or a fussy chef. Either way it was handled poorly  But damn the food is good

Order takeout from here!! Always walked past, finally ordered via UberEats a couple weeks ago and it was delicious. Love how they season their lobster roll. Fast delivery and tons of fries. Also love the cut and seasoning of the fries. Ordered again yesterday via Seamless. Again didn't skimp on the fries, delivery was fast, lobster was perfect but this time I got a biscuit that had lobster in it as a side. Filling, larger than I thought, came with 2 biscuits. Very good. Different from Red Lobsters biscuit but enjoyable. I've ordered pricer lobster lobster rolls for less meat and taste so 10/10 would recommend trying this spot.
Food was just ok 5 out of 10 not horrible but nothing I would go back to
I truly enjoyed the food, the  Atmosphere was great  staff was awesome .
First time here and I got the BK Lobster roll and lobster mac n cheese. Everything was so amazing! And its BYOB!!!

The food was great. Everyone I interacted with at the location was very professional. I ordered my food and went back to my car because I didn’t want to be rude as I was on my phone. When the food was ready, the young lady walked my food to my car. I was not expecting that. I will return to that location.
I had the loaded Lobster fries and the were absolutely amazing.....
Great food
Delicious lobster rolls. Biggie Roll. And the Connecticut Roll  are tasty. Lobster tastes fresh.

This was about my 4th time here and I've always ordered the buffalo wings. First two times they were incredible and that is what brought me back. But the last two times not as good - maybe a new chef. Plus, now they tell me fries do not come with the wings even though that is what it says on the menu. They may have lost a customer.
My 1st time there and really enjoyed the meal....Definitely will be back...The fried shrimp was delicious
Food was not good
Great Lobster rolls!
I tried this place already with a friend and I am addicted since then. I enjoy the great atmosphere and delightful food and drinks. Keep it up.
There's so many great things I can say about this place.   I will just leave with this, if you haven't had that Biggie or Flatbush roll, you missing out.
Very delicious food. I did not even know if this place until today and I am very happy I know it now.

Very disappointing. Man preparing the food not wearing his mask and when asked to do so...refused ...got very upaet and stated " im not going to kill myself". NEWS FLASH: We are still in the middle of a pandemic which unfortunately is killing many people, it is our responsibility to protect ourselves and others (those coming in to your place of business). To Management: this person is a representation of your business and unfortunately ill informed, careless and has no respect for patrons who want to support your business. ai attempted to reach the managemnt who didnt answer my calls and showed no regard for my complaint.
Good wasn't equal to the price & was still hungry at the end
Taste amazing!!! Great comfort food!🤤

I am a bit disappointed I wanted to give this place 5 stars this was my first time ordering here my sister was in from out of town and craved a lobster roll, so we selected here to eat for our group of three. I will make this easy we ordered (2) BK BIGGIE LOBSTER ROLLS, (1) SALMON ROLL, (3) DRINKS ALL MEALS CAME WITH A DRINK and (2)8 PIECE ORDERS OF WINGS.  Pros: lobsters roll and salmon roll flavor was good, wings were good, the french fries that came with the salmon roll were seasoned well from what I was told, drink were great (we had the sodas)  Cons: how we waited was not customer friendly we stood in the establishment for at least 10 minutes before someone came out after another customer started yelling " Hello, Hello!" I felt someone should have at least come out and said we will be with you momentarily or something, then it took forever to get the order we were told would take a half an hour it took longer. No one addressed this situation with a sorry for the wait or anything there was not enough lobster to call this a "biggie" anything the menu says it is double the meat I do not want to know what a regular would have in it. The fries were cold by the time we recieved our order.  Also suggest a wedge of lemon for the lobster roll would be nice
The wings was horrible, wasn't even done when I got home ,, I was so disappointed .. lobster roll good, but wings never again..

As a person who likes to try different restaurants I wish I would have read the reviews before giving this establishment my money.. The restaurant was loud and the staff was very rude.. But I let that slide (people have bad days) but when got my food home and ate it, I had to wash down my food with all the water I had in my refrigerator.. The food was very salty and the portion was small.. I ended up throwing the remaining lobster roll away.  This is one establishment I will not give anymore of my time and or money..

Really great food. Staff was nice and helpful about what to order. I do wish the portions were a little bigger. Got the lobster Mac which was amazing. Lobster was a good portion and the Mac was very cheesy and well seasoned. Glad they are open-great addition to Myrtle Ave.

Not my favorite...  like the previous poster said the food was salty but I also found the fried food to be dry. I enjoyed the lobster roll so I would probably order that again but I did not enjoy anything else. This was a delivery order so maybe the experience is better in the restaurant 🤷🏾‍♀️

Take out only! Only 2 customers are allowed in at a time for take-out orders.  No outdoor seating area available but many local parks that can be sat in if you need fresh air and a little lunch.  My companion and I ordered the BedStuy Biggie Lobster Roll and the Bay Ridge Lobster Roll. Omg....  Those rolls were dynamite. The roll is soft with a nice bite so it doesnt dilapidate. The Bay Ridge Roll had the perfect balance of sweet peppers to lobster to the little spicy mayo that I was scarfing the roll down in seconds. Lol maybe a little dramatic but I definitely was eating and singing the praises of the Lord.  The BedStuy Biggie had the lobster spilling out of the roll. I couldn't believe that it had juicy high quality lobster in it. Definitely worth a try if you are hungry.  Each roll came with fries and spicy mayo. The fries were a great way to start/ finish the meal. Spicy mayo fry combo made me never want to use ketchup again. Fries and spicy mayo for life!!!  Hope y'all get a chance to stop by and check it out!

Lobster Rolls are amazing. I tried the jerk Flatbush roll, fried crown heights rolls, and the Brooklyn Special Sauce Rolls. Also tried their signature sauce buffalo wings (Make sure you get your fries).
Very good

I wanted to patronize this restaurant,  as it is black owned, but I was very disappointed.  My daughter wanted a meal combo posted in their fb advertisement and was told  it didn't exist. She ordered the Brooklyn Biggie and I ordered crab legs. The food was poorly seasoned, dry, and they didnt include my corn. The two young ladies accepting the orders were not clear and gave conflicting information This was a take out order. Will not be going back.

The food was absolutely delicious.  The fried lobster is the best.   I went yesterday and placed an order 15 mins prior to arriving.  The person answering the phone said it would take 30 mins to be ready.  I arrived and waited over an hour.  Needless to say I was not happy.  And when I received my order, had I not checked my bag, I would have gotten home and not received my entire order.  However I must say the food is delicious.  I will give them the benefit of doubt and say maybe they had an extra busy day.  I hope to visit soon and upgrade to 5 stars.

THIS IS THE NEW ONE ON MYRTLE AVE.  MY DAUGHTERS WENT SATURDAY,GOT A VERY BAD ORDER,THE LOBSTER WAS CHEWY AND MAC HAD NO CHEESE,JUS HORRIBLE NOT FOR 100+$ THEIR ESSENTIAL WORKERS,WORKIN HARD FOR THEIR MONEY,I SAID CALL BACK TELL THEM OF UR DISPLEASURE. SHE DID AND WAS TOLD TO COME BACK YESTERDAY. SHE DID AND RECEIVED WHAT WE REALLY ORDERED. IT WAS BETTER JUS A SKIMPY ON THE LOBSTER ESP THE FRIED ONE,MORE BREAD&LETTUCE THEN LOBSTER.
Ordered The Biggie, Flatbush, & Salmon Roll. They were all extremely salty. Had the food not been salty it would have been good. Could not finish the entire order due to the excess salt.
Loved it brown girls winningggg food is delicious and customer service is superb the owner took my picture for the gram 🤎🖤
Love the food, great staff, nice atomsphere..

All I can say is LOBSTER BISCUITS!!!! OMG 😋😋🤤🤤🤤 The wait was kind of long, but expected. It was well worth the wait. Everything tasted AMAZING! I've never left a review on Google before, but I had to leave one for this amazing establishment. I had the lobster biscuits, shrimp, and the Bed-Stuy Biggie Roll..... I just taste tested everything and my tastebuds were extremely satisfied with what BK Lobster brought to them!

Take out -girl told me 20 mins and it took 50 mins. recommended food which was dry. They serve very small portions I literally had 15 French fries with my over cooked lobster dry roll without the lemon butter garlic sauce server said it came with. My friend as well had 6 shrimps and 15 fries. They had tarter sauce packets, you get a drop of ketchup and a drop of chipotle mayo in a container literally. 43 dollars. I would never again or recommend anyone to waste their money this place is a joke .DO NOT GO
This was my 1st time having a lobster roll!!!! I had the B.I.G.G.I.E ROLL and it was delicious!! I'm so happy I didn't waste my $$$$$ b/c it was worth every cent!!!!! You won't regret!

I just wanted to leave a review I was in this establishment a little earlier in the afternoon where I witness managers attacking there poor employees over the phone over a misunderstanding. The young lady that was in front of me tried to let the manger know she was talking to me,  just to mediate the situation but the manger insisted in a nasty manner manager to speak to the other employee who was now in tears and about to leave the store. I applaud the girl who tried to let them know I was in the store because it was very uncomfortable and unprofessional and I will never return to BK lobster again treat your team better you need them.

Just got the new hours 💃💃👌.. UPDATE 3/10/20 Sad to say had a horrible experience.  Lobster roll was horrible.  Order was incomplete,  bread barely toasted so Cold and the lobster meat was NOT as advertised for a Biggie. Disappointed👎
need more seats but food is good
Food was not good at all the fries were cold ima person who go to a lot of restaurants and this is not it the need to get it together

The interior is very inviting. Great design. A friend and I ordered lobster rolls. The lobster meat looked nothing like the rolls posted in the pics. The meat was chopped up and not one piece of lump meat was in either of our rolls. The meat was over seasoned and dry. Did I mention dry? Very dry lobster meat. On the brighter side of things, the bun was very good.
Awesome people and the atmosphere awesome. The music great. Bathroom clean.  Beautiful place for any occasion.

I waited 45mins for a lobster roll and biscuits. It was just me and one other person waiting during the day when they weren’t even busy. The “new” chef with the colored hair came to the bar several times with just one piece of the order at a time and had a very bad demeanor with the “new” waitress/bartender when she asked about the wait. The roll was not that good to wait 45 mins for and the biscuits wasn’t even done in the inside. I wouldn’t suggest this place.
It was very nice for my boys birthday party.

Where do I begin. For such a nice place we eat with plastic forks. Second the food was terrible I had the lobster roll and the lobster tasted like rubber. As for my boyfriend he had the lobster pasta and u know when pasta is fresh it was so oily and the noodles was hard. I jus was so upset and disappointed that I gave back the food paid the bill and left. Would never recommend this spot to anyone.

Walked in for take out after getting the menu slipped under my door. Was very happy with the bk sampler. Fries are good. Had an hour wait for it but the energy in the restaurant was good so we didnt mind much very satisfied with our food. Will return.

For the price of the meal I expected more. Utensils were plastic, napkins were thin and def from the $1store. Didn’t even have real cups! No soda, ice tea was in a bottle and I had to ask for water. The cook delivered the wrong food several times. Gave our order to them wrong table. I ordered the Salmon cakes, when they came out they were wet on the inside. The waitress said it was probably the egg used to bind the food! Then she wasn’t happy when asked to take it off the bill. Don’t foresee this place staying in business
Ordered take out. It was a decent amount of lobster.  The Classic and Connecticut   was a tad salty but other than that it was good
It Was Awesome,That Will Become On e Of My Regular Spots When I'm Out And About!!!!
Non-alcohol bar
Its something different Brooklyn needed.
My daughter love this place I hate the price..$$$💰

The customer service was AMAZING, Hawa was such a delight....Oh and as my Lobster roll tour continues, BK lobster is in a lane of its own. The seasoning set the tone!!!....BONUS-The fried Lobster SUPERB.
Food was amazing. Tastes Fresh. The service was great. Very hospitable...
Food, service was Gucci...
This place is amazing and the food is delicious. Oh and the atmosphere is so chill. The music is such a good vibe also. I think everyone should go check them out asap. Trust, u wont be disappointed.
The portions are small & in my opinion over priced its okay tasting I've had better

Relaxing atmosphere, amazing food (lobster rolls are excellent!), and overall a wonderful dining experience. The staff is friendly and the manager was very hands on and accommodating. Great location for takeout. BYOB for drinks when dining in.
The food was amazing! Great atmosphere and good service. The manager was amazing as well. I’m definitely visiting here again!
Celebrated my birthday here. Great atmosphere!!! Food is delicious and served in a timely manner. The manager was very accommodating as well.

Heard this was a good place and came here with my wife for a little birthday lunch. We came when they jus opened and the general manager Durrell opened the door and let us in. He took care of us until the other staff arrived. Let me jus say the food, delicious. We Had the lobster and waffles, shrimp and waffles and the loaded fries. The loaded fries had an ample amount of lobster and healthy amount of fries. The waffles where delicious and fluffy and the shrimp and lobster seasoned well. My wife truly enjoyed and she is quite picky. I give it 5 stars and will definitely come back. P.S. try the Main Root Sarsparilla.

Arrived at 8pm and took a seat at the bar. Waited 45min for a lobster roll and fries...Lobster roll was pretty good and flavorful....fries tasted a bit stale as if they've been sitting out all day.. that was a bit odd being that it was only 8pm.. While i waited for my meal, i wasn't offered a drink menu or even a complimentary glass of water. The 2 workers lacked people skills n that they didn't keep me updated with the status of my order.. i had to keep asking. Once my food arrived i asked that they add lettuce to my lobster roll. She then took it back to the kitchen, and a few mins later returned back to place my meal in the bag. I wanted to see what changed so i asked to see my food before she placed it in the bag... she waited until i opened the tray to tell me that they ran out of lettuce.. umm ok...Place has great potential. Please improve service.
Just  ok
Too expensive and food was OK could have been better
I understand this spot is new, but was it exterminated?!?!   If you’re looking for great food and service this isn’t the place to go. Waiting time was too long for bad food, and our waiter sucked!!

Too expensive! The restaurant was not crowded when I ordered. Yet the wait was longer than 15 mins. They started serving fries with the Lobster Rolls so the already expensive menu prices are $2-$3 more. They had no ketchup. The restaurant on Nostrand Ave. Could've gone to any cornerstore to buy ketchup for it's customers. The Mac and Cheese was cold at definetly NOT worth $15. Overall...its a no. Great space but way too expensive. To not offer lunch specials and or Happy Hour is dumb. That could bring in so many more potential customers.

Was by far one of my favorite places to dine. Quite a gem in a neighborhood overrun with nothing but low quality, and fast food options. They have several menu options to choose from and although they are a bit pricey, the friendly staff, amazing food, and timely service makes up for that. Quality can never be argued. I am disappointed because the last two times I've visited, I've noticed that the lobster rolls are now filled with 50% less lobster meat and the terra cotta chips have now been replaced with sweet potato fries. Definitely not an even exchange and although I will still patronize, it won't be as often. I do understand business, cost efficiency, and practicality so I'm still going to give a great review. Tuesdays and Thursdays are great if you're looking for a great vibe.
New business is maintaining 🤷🏾‍♀️They need some time to get things together  Poor service
Try the Bed Stuy Notorious B.I.G roll. It was on point! The service was good as well! Even got a chance to speak with the owner, he was cool!
A brand new permanent staple of the Brooklyn community.  Amazing food and the DJ is top notch.  Yo the oldies set was crazee.... I'll be back.

Absolutely delicious,  and I loved the layout its very semi family style and the parking at night wasn't bad at all , but let's get down to the food it was delicious jammed packed with lobster and the ginger beer was A1 perfect pairing.  I had the biggie roll it can use a bit more sauce or just drop the vegan butter and give me the real thing , but even without I can still honestly say I loved it and would order it again .
Love the BIGGIE Roll. Great vibe. Good service.

Went in today October 23rd... NO LOBSTER young girl at the counter sed, "they had an event yesterday...and 2 many ppl came"( huh) Ur a lobster spot... with no lobster... so we left and went across the street 2 Black Nile
First time eating there today the food is excellent and the staff is nice. Daddy - O from the group Stetsasonic son owns the restaurant.
Love it!!!

BK Sauce Lobster Roll - YUM. Nice decor. Chill spot.

I ordered the biggie lobster roll with and it definitely didn't disappoint.  One of the best side perks about bk lobster is the the themed nights I went on a Tuesday and for a very minuscule fee you can bring your own wine and certain spirits and enjoy the best atmosphere customer service & DJ I've come across in a very long while. The bathrooms are very clean theres parking after 7 out front and metered parking before . I'd definitely go back.
Fabulous, the food the atmosphere and music was great!!
Awesome Eats And Beautiful Environment

Great experience! Biggie Roll and Coney Island Rolls are my favorite. Stop by, you WON'T be disappointed.

Great service!!
amazing lobster roll. price was more than fair. Staff was friendly knowledgeable and efficient. Service was fast and accurate.
Ordered on seamless, food came ontime and was really good. Lobster Roll with coleslaw.

Brooklyn's Bedford Stuyvesant/Crown Heights has a new business in the neighborhood. Enter BK Lobster who invites everyone to come and experience lobster rolls the Brooklyn Way. It is conveniently located on Nostrand Ave between Herkimer Street and Atlantic Avenue. It is easily accessible by car, subway, and bus.  There are twelve different lobster roll choices to choose from. Some of the names of the lobster rolls are familiar names that we've heard before and some are named after Brooklyn neighborhoods. There is an $100 Golden Lobster Roll which consists of 3 Cold Water North Atlantic Gulf of Maine Lobster Tails wrapped in 24k Gold Edible Leafs, drizzled in vegan butter sauce..... sounds delightful. It is also served with 23K Gold Luxury Wine.  I believe that they will do great at this location. I wish them all the best with the success of their restaurant,
